WEBVTT

00:00:28.320 --> 00:00:31.896
so even a droplet of moisture
or, more likely, a grain of sand,

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:33.776
would cause it to short.

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:37.056
It was faulty, and most of the time
I had to restart it over and over

00:00:37.080 --> 00:00:38.296
before it worked.

00:00:38.320 --> 00:00:41.536
"Please not now,
please not now," I thought.

00:00:41.560 --> 00:00:45.176
The transporter shivered in the sand
and I held my breath.

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:47.496
Tiny, flat and black as a prayer stone,

00:00:47.520 --> 00:00:50.760
it buzzed softly and then
slowly rose from the sand.

00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:54.256
Finally, it produced
the baggage-lifting force.

00:00:54.280 --> 00:00:55.816
I grinned.

00:00:55.840 --> 00:00:57.920
Now I could make it
to the shuttle on time.

